JProcessing

Class Processing.PVector

  • java.lang.Object
    • JProcessing.Processing.PVector
  • Enclosing class:
    Processing

    public static class Processing.PVector
extends java.lang.Object
    PVector is a Class to Describe a Multi-dimensional Euclidean Vector.

    Vector is Defined as A Quantity having Direction as well as Magnitude.
    The Class PVector Stores Components of a Vector in a float Array. It also Provides Methods for Vector Math such as Dot Product, Cross Product, Calculating Direction and Magnitude.

    Unlike in Processing IDE, PVector Class in JProcessing are not Limited to Represent a 2 or 3 Dimensional Vector. Instead, Vector with any Dimension can be Stored in PVector and Performs Vector Calculations.
    The Magnitude of a PVector in the first 3 Dimensions can be Set and Assigned directly using x, y, and z. Vector with Dimension more than 3 should use .set(float[]), .set(double[]), and .array() to Set or Obtain its Magnitude.

    The Dimension of the Vector can be Specified in Constructor PVector(Number). The Max Dimension Allowed is 32768.

    Since:
    1.0
    See Also:
    PVector in Processing IDE

      • PVector

        public PVector(double[] component)
        Construct a multi-dimensional vector using the data from a double array as its components.

        Since all components of PVector are stored in the type of float, all entries of component will be converted to float value, and the extra precisions will be lost.

        Parameters:
        component - an array representing all components of a vector
